            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Colonel
                            <persName type="to">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-29">29 September
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1579. Second solution where equipment is retained by United States Reurad 81589
                    for subsequent declaration as surplus and sale to Chinese Government appears
                    most workable here also.</p>
            </div>
